Good news — on .NET 10 SDK, **you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property is the .NET 9 (and earlier) workaround to make `dotnet test` talk to MTP projects.

Instead, add a `"test"` section to your `global.json`:

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

Then remove `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` from your `.csproj`.

**Key difference**: With .NET 10's native mode, MTP arguments are passed directly (e.g., `dotnet test --report-trx`). You no longer need the `--` separator that .NET 9 required.

